    "This method not only helps resolve slight spelling variations, such as \"Jew\" and \"jew\", but also standardizes elements with different names referring to the same concept, such as \"LGBT\" and \"LGBTQ+\".",
    "To prevent over-merging, we set a relatively high similarity threshold.",
    "The benefits of entity resolution are twofold.",
    "On the one hand, it reduces noise by eliminating unnecessary spelling differences and retaining representative expressions supported by most elements.",
    "On the other hand, it decreases the overall size of the graph, which in turn enhances the efficiency of graph retrieval."
